  "texts": [
    "We do not consider hydrogen atoms in our computations.",
    "Unfortunately, computing the MCES is provably hard, and it is considered highly unlikely that an efficient algorithm for this problem exists.",
    "Precisely speaking, the MCES problem is NP-hard, as it generalizes subgraph isomorphism which, in turn, generalizes the clique problem.",
    "As MCES is clearly in NP, it is NP-complete.",
    "Next, an \"efficient algorithm\" is an algorithm with running time polynomial in the size of the instance, that is, the number of edges or nodes of the two graphs for the MCES problem."
  ],
